column516: After substantial reductions to the Library budget in FY10 and FY11, the municipal appropriation saw a large restoration in FY12. Hours of service were restored to 50 per week. The Children\'s Librarian position, vacant since June of 2010, was filled in late August 2011. Children\'s and teen programming increased substantially, causing a dramatic increase in circulation. The Library\'s LSTA grant, \"Serving Tweens and Teens\" was in it\'s second year in FY12, resulting in an increase in teen participation in library programs. The Library also received generous private donations which funded new public computers, resulting in positive user experiences.
column525: Friends of the Abington Public Library
Citizens Library Auxilliary
